J/A+A/531/A60       WASP-31b photometry and radial velocities  (Anderson+, 2011)
================================================================================
WASP-31b: a low-density planet transiting a metal-poor, late-F-type dwarf star.
    Anderson D.R., Collier Cameron A., Hellier C., Lendl M., Lister T.A.,
    Maxted P.F.L., Queloz D., Smalley B., Smith A.M.S., Triaud A.H.M.J.,
    West R.G., Brown D.J.A., Gillon M., Pepe F., Pollacco D., Segransan D.,
    Street R.A., Udry S.
   <Astron. Astrophys. 531, A60 (2011)>
   =2011A&A...531A..60A
================================================================================
ADC_Keywords: Binaries, eclipsing ; Planets ; Radial velocities ; Photometry
Keywords: binaries: eclipsing - planetary systems - stars: individual: WASP-31

Abstract:
    We report the discovery of the low-density, transiting giant planet
    WASP-31b. The planet is 0.48 Jupiter masses and 1.55 Jupiter radii. It
    is in a 3.4-day orbit around a metal-poor, late-F-type, V=11.7 dwarf
    star, which is a member of a common proper motion pair. In terms of
    its low density, WASP-31b is second only to WASP-17b, which is a more
    highly irradiated planet of similar mass.

Description:
    The host star WASP-31 was observed by WASP-South during 2006 to 2011.
    The WASP photometry was corrected for blending with a star 4.1mag
    fainter, located 35arcsec away. Spectroscopic measurements were
    obtained using the CORALIE spectrograph mounted on the Euler-Swiss
    1.2-m telescope (La Silla, Chile) and the HARPS spectrograph mounted
    on the ESO 3.6-m telescope (La Silla, Chile) to confirm the planetary
    nature of the eclipsing body and to measure its mass. A total of 47
    measurements were obtained by CORALIE, 1 of which fell during transit,
    and 10 measurements were obtained by HARPS. The data are plotted in
    Figures 1, 2 and 3.

Objects:
    -----------------------------------------------------
       RA   (2000)   DE      Designation(s)
    -----------------------------------------------------
    11 17 45.4   -19 03 17   WASP 31 = TYC 6087-1053-1
    -----------------------------------------------------

